<HR><P>
<H2>Character recognition</H2>
<P><UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://world.std.com/~jrward/pens/biblio80.htm">Annotated
bibliography in on-line character recognition</A>, J. R. Ward.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cast.uni-linz.ac.at/st/staff/burge/voronoi.html">Grouping words and multi-part symbols</A>.
M. Burge and G. Monagan use Voronoi diagrams for document analysis.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cis.temple.edu/fuh.html">Medial axis
transformation and its application to seal imprint verification</A>.
Y.-M. Fuh uses medial axis skeletonization as part of a method for detecting
forgeries in Chinese signature blocks.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://members.aol.com/tesarna/">Tesarna Typesetter Program</A>
uses medial axes to produce carved lettering by a computer controlled router.
<P>
<li><a href="http://164.195.100.11/netacgi/nph-Parser?p=1&u=/netahtml/search-adv.htm&r=1&f=G&l=50&d=PALL&S1=5159645.WKU.">US
Patent 5159645</a> performs character recognition by using convex hulls
to find the counters in each character. A similar idea also occurs in 
<a href="http://164.195.100.11/netacgi/nph-Parser?p=1&u=/netahtml/search-adv.htm&r=1&f=G&l=50&d=PALL&S1=4817166.WKU.">Patent
4817166</a>.
<p>
<li><a href="http://164.195.100.11/netacgi/nph-Parser?p=1&u=/netahtml/search-adv.htm&r=1&f=G&l=50&d=PALL&S1=5483606.WKU.">US
Patent 5483606</a> describes a method of registering (lining up) copied
pages with each other in a copying machine, using the convex hulls of
images of the pages.
<p>
</UL><HR><P>
